cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with model-theoretic properties of a variation of monadic first-order logic. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the expressiveness of a logic that includes the generalised quantifier $\exists^\infty$, which could be relevant to AI applications. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possibility as the paper deals with syntactically defined fragments of logic and decidable properties of sentences. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) could also be relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of deciding certain semantic properties of the logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but could be relevant if the paper's results are applied to the development of programming languages.
